     abstract = "{Context. Ultra-hot Jupiters (UHJs) are gas giant exoplanets that are
        strongly irradiated by their star, setting intense molecular
        dissociation that leads to atmospheric chemistry dominated by
        ions and atoms. These conditions inhibit day-to-night heat
        redistribution, which results in high temperature contrasts.
